  "Name": "Users with Kerberos pre-authentication disabled",
  "ScriptName": "UsersWithPreAuth",
  "ShortName": "SI000027",
  "Description": "This indicator identifies users with Kerberos pre-authentication disabled, which exposes them to potential ASREP-Roasting attacks, such as 'Kerberoasting'.",
  "CategoryId": "2",
  "Weight": 5,
  "Severity": "Warning",
  "Schedule": "3d",
  "Impact": 5,
  "LikelihoodOfCompromise": "<p>If an account has Kerberos pre-authentication disabled, it makes it easier for attackers to send dummy requests to a DC to try and crack its Ticket Granting Ticket (TGT).</p>\n      <h3>References</h3>\n      <p><a href=\"https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/archive/technet-wiki/23559.kerberos-pre-authentication-why-it-should-not-be-disabled\" target=\"_blank\">Kerberos Pre-Authentication: Why It Should Not Be Disabled | Microsoft Learn</a></p>\n      <p><a href=\"https://www.cert.ssi.gouv.fr/uploads/ad_checklist.html#vuln_kerberos_properties_preauth_priv\" target=\"_blank\">Kerberos preauthentication disabled for privileged accounts\n | ANSSI</a></p>",
